<TITLE> Shuvo, Mendis propels Ispahani </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 4 (bdnews24.com)  Fifties from Shamsur Rahman Shuvo and Jeevan Mendis propelled Ispahani Sporting Club to a convincing 50-run win over Pirates of Chittagong in the Port City League Twenty20 tournament in Chittagong on Monday. Brothers Union, who shared points with Chittagong Abahani in their opening match, also recorded a 46-win over Mohammedan Sporting Club at the MA Aziz Stadium. After put in to bat, Ispahani posted a challenging 175-5 in the stipulated 20 overs after Shuvo and Mendis added 114 runs for the second wicket. Shuvo, who was named in the ICC Twenty20 World Cup squad on Monday, celebrated his call up putting on on 53 runs for the opening stand with Fazle Rabby, who struck 25 off 20 deliveries that included four fours. Shuvo and Mendis then dominated the Pirates bowlers before left-arm spinner Surawardi stopped Shuvo, who hammered 71 off just 49 balls studded with eight fours and two sixes. Mendis was the fifth batsman to go for 65 off 48 balls featuring four fours and three sixes and then Ispahani were restricted to 175-5 in 20 overs. Pirates of Chittagong were reduced to 46-4 in 7 overs but middle order batsmen Naeem Islam (17), Waqas Ahmed (19) and Surawardi (29) produced some resistance to help Pirates finish on 125 with two balls to go. Monir Hossain Khan (3/18) and Monir Hossain (2/11) Dar shared five wickets. In the second match, Brothers chose to bat and put up a fighting 136-9 in 20 overs with Tushar Imran top scoring with 29 off 24 balls with the help of three fours. Opener Mehrab Hossain Jr (20 off 13 balls), one-down Jehan Mubarak (24 off 23 balls) and Rezajul Karim (14 off 20 balls) were other Brothers run-getters. In reply, Mohammedan lost both openers with the scoreboard reading 17-2 in 2.4 and and eventually were bundled out for 90 in 18 overs. bd
